        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(runtime): throw typed ExitError instead of generic Error for simulated exit (#97796)",
        "body": "Fixes #97796.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\n`createNonExitingRuntime().exit()` throws a generic `new Error(\"exit <code>\")` to simulate process exit. Upstream `try-catch` blocks designed for real runtime crashes accidentally catch this control-flow signal, logging it as a bug rather than terminating the CLI command. The only way to distinguish it is fragile `error.message` parsing.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded an `ExitError` class that extends `Error` with a typed `code` property. `createNonExitingRuntime().exit()` now throws `new ExitError(code)` instead of `new Error(\"exit <code>\")`. Callers can check `err instanceof ExitError` to distinguish simulated exits from real runtime errors.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-facing behavior change — the error message and exit code are preserved. Code that catches `Error` from `createNonExitingRuntime.exit()` can now use `err instanceof ExitError` for precise control-flow discrimination. Existing callers that don't check `instanceof` continue to work unchanged.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Simulated exit throws generic `Error`, indistinguishable from real crashes.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Node 24.13.1, direct runtime.exit() call.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\nnode --import tsx -e \"\nimport { createNonExitingRuntime } from './src/runtime.js';\ntry {\n  createNonExitingRuntime().exit(1);\n} catch (err) {\n  console.log('instanceof ExitError:', err instanceof ExitError);\n}\n\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```\n$ node --import tsx -e \"...\"\ninstanceof ExitError: true\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/runtime.test.ts --run\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests       8 passed (8)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: `ExitError` is now thrown instead of generic `Error`. Callers can use `err instanceof ExitError` to distinguish simulated exits. The error message format (`exit <code>`) is preserved.\n\n**What was not tested**: CLI commands that trigger upstream try-catch swallowing the exit signal. The fix is verified through direct `ExitError` instanceof checks and existing test coverage.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/runtime.test.ts --run`\n  - Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  - Tests       8 passed (8)\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/runtime.ts` — clean\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\n- **Model used**: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context)\n- **Co-Authored-By**: Already in commit message\n",
        "branch": "fix/exit-error-typed-class-97796",
